history.content: I had this same schedule as a third year (including the 20 hour work week) and I think it really depends on how much time you can invest in 70/how comfortable you feel with mathematics in general. If you're not very good at it (like me), it can be a very rough schedule but survivable. It's definitely doable though.

How difficult would 70, 161, and 168 be, with a light humanities class? I know the workload for 70 is supposed to be pretty bad, but what are the workloads like for 161 and 168? Would it be better to take 70, 168, and IB 160 (my natural science)? I’m graduating next spring, so I have to take three technicals. I’m leaning towards 70/161/168 because it gives me a very easy spring semester (and a very nice class time schedule for fall), but I don’t want to overload myself for fall. I also work 20hr/week for reference.
history.subject: Schedule Difficulty
